,"ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P8":{"blocking":false,"budget_tokens":868000,"name":"reviewability","plan_tokens":1198,"ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P9":{"applicable":true,"blocking":false,"file_impact":2,"name":"file-impact-coverage","ran":true,"status":"pass"}},"llm_ran":true,"metrics":{"claim_path":"no-llm/no-network (structural; the fast claim check is a local HMAC verify)","det_ms":214.4,"llm_calls":28,"llm_ms":527242.8,"total_ms":527551.1,"verify_requests":8},"remediation":{"baseline":"sidecar","eligible":false,"reasons":{"code_unchanged":false,"plan_changed":false,"registry_unchanged":false,"sidecar_baseline":false,"within_window":false}},"routing":{"agent_tier":["A1","E4","G1G2","G6","G7","T1","T10","T11","T13","T14","T3","T5c","T8","removal-rationale"],"single_turn":["COH","E1","E2","E3","E5","E6","F1","G5","T2","T4","T5b","T5e","T6","T7","T9","hedge"]}},"findings":[{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Resolve the missing `docs/ticket-model.md` pointer target: either (a) confirm ticket-model.md will be created by a dependency story before this one merges, (b) substitute an existing doc that covers the ticket model (e.g. `docs/user-guide.md` or `docs/event-schema.md`), or (c) remove the pointer from the AGENTS.md plan and inline only the essential rule.","cohort":["G6"],"criteria":["G6"],"decision":"block","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan text: 'POINTER: ticket-model→docs/ticket-model.md'","docs/ directory listing: no ticket-model.md file exists","search_files for 'ticket-model.md' in docs/ returns no hits"],"finding":"The De-risking POINTER list names 'ticket-model→docs/ticket-model.md' as a target for an AGENTS.md one-line pointer, but docs/ticket-model.md does not exist in the repository. An executor following the plan would write a dead link in AGENTS.md.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fa49d4ea5b9c4514f","impact":0.85,"is_primary":null,"location":"De-risking results — POINTER list: 'ticket-model→docs/ticket-model.md'","norm_id":"n67d81d84ae272895","priority":0.6611,"reason":"high-priority+criterion-opted-in","scenarios":["An implementer writing AGENTS.md inserts a pointer '→ docs/ticket-model.md' which resolves to a 404 for any reader following the link.","A reviewer running the AC's 'reviewer confirms pointer-not-duplicate per topic' check discovers the target is missing and the AC fails."],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"Replace 'ticket-model→docs/ticket-model.md' in the POINTER list with an existing authoritative source (e.g. docs/user-guide.md covers ticket-model concepts) or note that this pointer depends on a re-home story that creates docs/ticket-model.md and make that dependency explicit in the Scope/Depends-on line.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.7778,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"yes","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"low","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"high","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add `docs/llm-framework.md` and `docs/plan-review-gate.md` edits to the 'In:' scope list, and add explicit proof commands (e.g. `rg 'LLM-agent-operations\\|completion.verification' docs/llm-framework.md docs/plan-review-gate.md`) to the stowaway re-homing AC.","cohort":["E3","E5","G5"],"criteria":["E3"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["\"In: new AGENTS.md, rewritten CLAUDE.md. Out: CLAUDE.md.local (its own story)...\" — no mention of edits to docs/llm-framework.md or docs/plan-review-gate.md","\"the two stowaways are re-homed to llm-framework.md / plan-review-gate.md\" — asserted as AC but has no proof command, unlike all other ACs","\"Two stowaways...must be RE-HOMED, not merely relocated\" — confirms this is required work, but Scope does not list it"],"finding":"The 'In:' scope list names only 'new AGENTS.md, rewritten CLAUDE.md', but the plan also requires writing/appending content to two external docs files (docs/llm-framework.md, docs/plan-review-gate.md) to re-home the stowaways. These are unacknowledged deliverables in the scope declaration, and the revised ACs assert they are done but supply no proof command to verify it — unlike every other AC which has an explicit `rg`/`wc -l` proof.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f8563a0745ec0b806","impact":1.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Scope section ('In:' list) and Revised Acceptance Criteria bullet 2","norm_id":"ne8960b501eb612c5","priority":0.6667,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["An agent executing this plan sees 'In: AGENTS.md, CLAUDE.md' and skips editing the target docs, leaving stowaway content stranded or duplicated.","A reviewer checking ACs finds no `rg` proof for the stowaway landing; the criterion is unverifiable."],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"Update Scope: \"In: new `AGENTS.md`, rewritten `CLAUDE.md`, stowaway content appended to `docs/llm-framework.md` and `docs/plan-review-gate.md`.\"\nUpdate AC: add proving line: \"`rg -l 'agent.operations' docs/llm-framework.md` returns a match; `rg -l 'completion.verification' docs/plan-review-gate.md` returns a match; neither phrase remains in `CLAUDE.md`.\"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.6667,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"yes","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"missing_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"low","internal_conflict":"low","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] For each stowaway re-homing, specify: (a) the exact section/location in the target doc where the content lands, (b) a merge rule for pre-existing adjacent content (append-only vs. merge vs. replace), and (c) a proving command (e.g. `rg -l 'agent.operations' docs/llm-framework.md`) in the Revised AC.","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan text: 'the LLM-agent-operations paragraph → docs/llm-framework.md; the completion-verification close-gate blockquote → docs/plan-review-gate.md'","docs/llm-framework.md and docs/plan-review-gate.md both already exist (confirmed by docs/ directory listing and file reads); both already contain related content","docs/plan-review-gate.md already references the completion-verification close gate in its opening paragraph ('The plan-review gate is the inverse of the completion-verification close gate')","Revised AC2: 'the two stowaways are re-homed to llm-framework.md / plan-review-gate.md' — no proving command, no merge protocol for pre-existing content","No fallback rule: what if the content already exists there? what if appending creates duplication?"],"finding":"The plan mandates re-homing two 'stowaways' (LLM-agent-operations paragraph → `docs/llm-framework.md`; completion-verification close-gate blockquote → `docs/plan-review-gate.md`) but specifies no fallback or decision rule for an executor when those target docs already contain conflicting/adjacent content — e.g. if `docs/plan-review-gate.md` already documents the close gate in a different form. The Revised AC asserts this as a criterion but provides no proving command and no protocol for the append-or-merge decision.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f4176000bbd337107","impact":1.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"De-risking results — 'Two stowaways' paragraph; Revised Acceptance Criteria bullet 2","norm_id":"nacf95afafeb71f65","priority":0.6667,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["An executor appends the completion-verification close-gate blockquote verbatim to docs/plan-review-gate.md, which already discusses the same gate — producing a duplicated, inconsistent description.","A reviewer cannot verify the AC is met because no proving command (e.g. `rg 'completion-verification' docs/plan-review-gate.md`) is specified."],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.6667,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"yes","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"missing_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"low","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"medium"}}},{"block_threshold":0.75,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Verify that `docs/ticket-model.md` will exist before or during this story's execution (either created by the re-home story dependency or created here), or remove `docs/ticket-model.md` from the POINTER list and adjust where ticket-model content lives.","cohort":["E4"],"criteria":["E4"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["list_directory('docs') shows no ticket-model.md file","search_files('ticket-model', 'docs') returns zero matches for any file named ticket-model.md","Plan states: 'POINTER: ticket-model→`docs/ticket-model.md`' as the home for ticket-model content that will be removed from AGENTS.md"],"finding":"The plan's POINTER table lists 'ticket-model→`docs/ticket-model.md`' as a one-line pointer AGENTS.md will use (instead of restating ticket-model content inline), but `docs/ticket-model.md` does not exist in the repository. This is a scope-exclusion claim: the plan excludes ticket-model content from AGENTS.md on the premise that a canonical doc exists to point to — but the target is absent.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f3d64ec9092a4ede7","impact":0.85,"is_primary":null,"location":"De-risking results section — POINTER list: 'ticket-model→`docs/ticket-model.md`'","norm_id":"n9295383831457f80","priority":0.6611,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["An executor writing AGENTS.md creates a one-line pointer to docs/ticket-model.md, but clicking/reading that pointer leads to a 404 — the content is neither in AGENTS.md nor in the pointed-to doc.","The 'docs homes must exist first' dependency (Depends on: the re-home story) may be supposed to create this file, but if that story hasn't shipped, AGENTS.md has a dead pointer."],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.7778,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"yes","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","n