'In:' to include writes to `docs/llm-framework.md` and `docs/plan-review-gate.md`, and add a revised AC verifying both files contain the re-homed content.","cohort":["COH","E1","T4"],"criteria":["COH","E1"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Scope: 'In: new AGENTS.md, rewritten CLAUDE.md. Out: CLAUDE.local.md (its own story)'","De-risking: 'the LLM-agent-operations paragraph → docs/llm-framework.md; the completion-verification close-gate blockquote → docs/plan-review-gate.md'","No AC checks that llm-framework.md or plan-review-gate.md actually contain the re-homed content after the change."],"finding":"The Scope section defines deliverables as 'In: new AGENTS.md, rewritten CLAUDE.md' only, but the De-risking section adds two additional write operations — re-homing content to `docs/llm-framework.md` and `docs/plan-review-gate.md` — that are outside the stated scope. Neither the Scope nor the AC set has a criterion verifying these re-homing operations are complete, leaving them as uncovered work.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f626ab25b7748efc6","impact":1.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Scope section ('In: new AGENTS.md, rewritten CLAUDE.md') vs De-risking section ('Two stowaways ... must be RE-HOMED ... to docs/llm-framework.md / docs/plan-review-gate.md')","norm_id":"n24c376691fe37f35","priority":0.5,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["An implementer reads Scope and believes touching only AGENTS.md + CLAUDE.md is sufficient; the stowaways are never re-homed and AGENTS.md's pointers to those docs are dead links.","A reviewer cannot verify completion because no AC covers the re-homing writes."],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"Add to Scope 'In:': '`docs/llm-framework.md` (add LLM-agent-operations paragraph), `docs/plan-review-gate.md` (add completion-verification close-gate blockquote).' Add AC: '`docs/llm-framework.md` contains the LLM-agent-operations content and `docs/plan-review-gate.md` contains the completion-verification blockquote previously in CLAUDE.md.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.5,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"missing_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"medium","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Collapse to one canonical AC set (remove or strike-through the original ACs) and restore the `rg -c 'Gerrit|module-size|Serena|worktree' AGENTS.md` proving command in the revised set to verify inline content presence.","cohort":["E2","E6","F1"],"criteria":["E2","E6"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Original AC: 'rebar-internal dev specifics (Gerrit, module-size, Serena, local-dev-env, worktree/venv, CI-before-close, signing) are present in AGENTS.md. Proving: rg -c ...'","Revised ACs: this check is absent — no proving command verifies inline content presence","'Revised Acceptance Criteria (supersede/refine the ones above)' — 'supersede' implies old ones are void but they remain in the doc"],"finding":"Two coexisting sets of ACs ('Acceptance Criteria' and 'Revised Acceptance Criteria (supersede/refine the ones above)') remain in the plan. An executor cannot tell definitively which set is canonical — the revised set drops the `rg -c 'Gerrit|module-size|Serena|worktree' AGENTS.md` check that proved rebar-internal content is present, creating a verifiability gap if only the revised ACs are used.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fd8ad35a5c7aa26a1","impact":0.67,"is_primary":null,"location":"'Acceptance Criteria' section and 'De-risking results / Revised Acceptance Criteria' section","norm_id":"n929edb8a78f556d0","priority":0.4188,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["Executor uses only revised ACs, never verifies that Gerrit/Serena/worktree content actually landed in AGENTS.md","Executor uses both sets and double-counts work or encounters contradictions"],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"Delete the original 'Acceptance Criteria' block and add to the revised ACs: '- [ ] rebar-internal specifics (Gerrit, module-size, Serena, worktree/venv, CI-before-close, signing) are inline in AGENTS.md. Proving: `rg -c \"Gerrit\" AGENTS.md && rg -c \"Serena\" AGENTS.md && rg -c \"worktree\" AGENTS.md` — each exits 0.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"medium","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Clarify in scope/AC2 whether this plan authors the stowaway content into llm-framework.md and plan-review-gate.md, or only adds AGENTS.md pointer lines to files the prerequisite re-home story already populated.","cohort":["E2","E6","F1"],"criteria":["E2"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'Two stowaways wedged under CLAUDE.md's \"Session logs\" heading must be RE-HOMED, not merely relocated: the LLM-agent-operations paragraph → docs/llm-framework.md; the completion-verification close-gate blockquote → docs/plan-review-gate.md'","'Depends on: the import spike (mechanism) and the re-home story (docs homes must exist first)'","Revised AC2: 'the two stowaways are re-homed to llm-framework.md / plan-review-gate.md' — active voice implies this plan does it, but the dependency says those files pre-exist"],"finding":"The revised AC2 states 'the two stowaways are re-homed to llm-framework.md / plan-review-gate.md' but the plan also says this plan 'Depends on: the re-home story (docs homes must exist first).' It is unclear whether this plan is responsible for re-homing the stowaways (authoring content into those files) or merely adding pointers to files the prerequisite story already populated. An executor cannot determine whether writing stowaway content is in scope for this ticket.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f1bb3f309d0c04d02","impact":0.67,"is_primary":null,"location":"De-risking results section ('Two stowaways...') and Revised AC2","norm_id":"n9a4a60adddcd3adf","priority":0.4188,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["Executor assumes re-homing is done by prerequisite story and only adds pointers — stowaways are never actually moved","Executor attempts to author content into docs/ files, duplicating or conflicting with the prerequisite story's output"],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"medium","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"medium"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Collapse to one canonical AC set (delete or strike-through the original AC block), and restore the `rg -c 'Gerrit|module-size|Serena|worktree' AGENTS.md` proving command in the Revised ACs so an executor can unambiguously verify that rebar-internal content is present inline.","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Original AC: 'rebar-internal dev specifics (Gerrit, module-size, Serena, local-dev-env, worktree/venv, CI-before-close, signing) are present in AGENTS.md. Proving: `rg -c 'Gerrit|module-size|Serena|worktree' AGENTS.md` > 0 for each.'","Revised AC: this inline-content verification is absent — no proving command for rebar-internal topics survives into the revised set","'Revised Acceptance Criteria (supersede/refine the ones above)' — both sets remain in the document simultaneously with no deletion/strikethrough of the original","Instruction-locality antipattern: operative protocol split across two non-adjacent sections"],"finding":"The plan contains two coexisting, partially-conflicting Acceptance Criteria blocks — the original '## Acceptance Criteria' section and 'Revised Acceptance Criteria (supersede/refine the ones above)' embedded inside 'De-risking results'. An LLM executor cannot resolve which set is operative: the revised set drops the `rg -c 'Gerrit|module-size|Serena|worktree' AGENTS.md` proving command from the original, so an executor using only the revised ACs would silently skip verifying that the plan's primary deliverable (rebar-internal inline content) actually landed. The decision protocol is split across two sections with no merge rule.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fa863fb605a26fc46","impact":0.67,"is_primary":null,"location":"## Acceptance Criteria section vs. De-risking results — Revised Acceptance Criteria subsection","norm_id":"nec943909b0dc3dc2","priority":0.4188,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["An agent executor reads the plan top-to-bottom, treats the Revised ACs as operative, never verifies that Gerrit/Serena/worktree content landed, and declares done — the primary deliverable value (rebar-internal inline guidance) is silently absent.","An agent executor attempts to satisfy both AC sets, hits contradictions between them, and produces an indeterminate result."],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"Remove the original '## Acceptance Criteria' block entirely. In the Revised ACs, add: '- [ ] rebar-internal specifics (Gerrit, module-size, Serena, worktree/venv, CI-before-close, signing) are inline in AGENTS.md. Proving: `rg -c \"Gerrit\" AGENTS.md && rg -c \"Serena\" AGENTS.md && rg -c \"worktree\" AGENTS.md` — each exits 0.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"medium","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Enumerate the specific doc filenames that 'the re-home story' creates for the 'native topics' category (e.g. `docs/ticket-model.md`, `docs/session-log.md`) so an executor can write concrete one-line pointers without out-of-plan research.","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan text: '…replaces every section that has an authoritative doc with a one-line docs/…md pointer (…the native topics → the docs created in the re-home story)'","No enumeration of which docs the re-home story creates appears anywhere in this plan","The De-risking POINTER list does not include an entry for 'native topics', leaving the What-section claim unresolvable","Absence: no search hit for 'native topics' or 'docs created in the re-home story' in the codebase"],"finding":"The What section references 'the native topics → the docs created in the re-home story' as a pointer target category, but never names those docs. An LLM executor following the INLINE/POINTER decision taxonomy cannot determine which files to point to for 'native topics', making that pointer category unresolvable without out-of-plan research.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f01bbcc4783e5513b","impact":0.67,"is_primary":null,"location":"## What section: 'the native topics → the docs created in the re-home story'","norm_id":"n2f5c69955af95539","priority":0.4188,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["An agent executor cannot write the AGENTS.md 'native topics' pointers because the target filenames are never stated; they must guess or invent filenames, producing links that may be dead."],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"medium"}}},{"block_threshold":null,"blocking_enabled":null,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["P6"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["1 criterion line(s) bundle multiple deliverables with 'and' (split so each is independently verifiable).","verify command `wc -l AGENTS.md` inspects output with `wc` but asserts nothing — add an exit-code or comparison (-q, [ \"$(...)\" -eq N ], jq -e) so a failure is observable","verify command `wc -l CLAUDE.md` inspects output with `wc` but asserts nothing — add an exit-code or comparison (-q, [ \"$(...)\" -eq N ], jq -e) so a failure is observable","verify command `wc -l AGENTS.md` inspects output with `wc` but asserts nothing — add an exit-code or comparison (-q, [ \"$(...)\" -eq N ], jq -e) so a failure is observable","verify command `wc -l CLAUDE.md` inspects output with `wc` but asserts nothing — add an exit-code or comparison (-q, [ \"$(...)\" -eq N ], jq -e) so a failure is observable"],"finding":"Acceptance-criteria / definition-of-done quality issues.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f607dd457c67f9209","impact":0.4,"is_primary":null,"location":"","norm_id":"ned06ebc801a522e3","priority":0.4,"reason":null,"scenarios":[],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Split compound criteria, replace subjective terms with observable outcomes, and state how each is verified.","tier":"DET","validity":1.0,"verification":null},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add a proving command for the Gerrit section length, e.g. `awk '/^## Git/{f=1} f{n++} /^##[^#]/ && !/^## Git/{f=0} END{print n}' AGENTS.md` and assert the result ≤ 55.","cohort":["E2","E6","F1"],"criteria":["E6"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'wc -l AGENTS.md ≤ 200 (target ~150-170); the Git/Gerrit section is ≤~55 lines and defers the full recipe to CONTRIBUTING.md'","No proving command is given for the section-level line count"],"finding":"Revised AC1 requires 'the Git/Gerrit section is ≤~55 lines' but provides no proving command to measure it. Unlike `wc -l AGENTS.md` which counts the whole file, counting a named section requires a command the plan does not specify.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f3efad504511c07af","impact":0.55,"is_primary":null,"location":"Revised Acceptance Criteria — AC1: 'the Git/Gerrit section is ≤~55 lines'","norm_id":"nd13109e157609b05","priority":0.3438,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["Executor ships a 90-line Gerrit block (making AGENTS.md ~220 lines total) and the whole-file wc passes only because other sections were trimmed — the condensation decision goes unverified"],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"Proving: `awk '/^## .*[Gg]errit|^## .*[Gg]it/{f=1;n=0} f{n++} /^## / && !/^## .*[Gg]errit|^## .*[Gg]it/{if(f)print n; f=0}' AGENTS.md` — assert output ≤ 55.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add to the Revised ACs an explicit verification step (e.g., grep) confirming module-size, Serena, worktree/venv, CI-before-close, and signing content are present in AGENTS.md, since the Revised ACs that supersede the initial ones currently omit this check.","cohort":["COH","E1","T4"],"criteria":["E1"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Initial AC#2: 'rebar-internal dev specifics (Gerrit, module-size, Serena, local-dev-env, worktree/venv, CI-before-close, signing) are present in AGENTS.md. Proving: rg -c 'Gerrit|module-size|Serena|worktree' AGENTS.md > 0 for each.'","Revised AC#1: 'wc -l AGENTS.md ≤ 200 (target ~150-170); the Git/Gerrit section is ≤ ~55 lines and defers the full recipe to CONTRIBUTING.md.' — no mention of module-size, Serena, worktree, CI-before-close, signing.","What section: 'keeps rebar-INTERNAL dev specifics inline — Gerrit split-remote workflow, module-size policy, Serena navigation, local-dev-env, worktree/venv discipline, CI-before-close, signing'"],"finding":"The Revised Acceptance Criteria (which 'supersede/refine' the initial ones) drop explicit verification of five rebar-internal specifics — module-size policy, Serena navigation, worktree/venv discipline, CI-before-close, and signing — that are described work in the What section and were covered by the initial AC#2 grep command. After supersession, no AC verifies these items are present in AGENTS.md.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f489f7c61fa1aa83c","impact":0.55,"is_primary":null,"location":"Initial AC #2 ('rebar-internal dev specifics ... module-size, Serena, worktree/venv, CI-before-close, signing') vs Revised AC #1 (covers only size and Gerrit condensation)","norm_id":"nccce3d6781e5f359","priority":0.3438,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["Implementer satisfies only the revised ACs (size + Gerrit + pointer + lint), ships AGENTS.md missing Serena navigation or module-size policy, and the plan is marked complete despite missing described content."],"severity":"major","suggested_fix":"Append to Revised AC #1 or add a new item: 'AGENTS.md contains inline sections for module-size policy, Serena navigation, worktree/venv discipline, CI-before-close, and signing. Proving: `rg -c \"module.size|Serena|worktree|CI.before|sign\" AGENTS.md` > 0 for each term.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"low","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add an explicit back-out plan for the CLAUDE.md rewrite (e.g., 'if @AGENTS.md import is verified non-functional in any target agent, revert CLAUDE.md to its previous content via git revert and re-evaluate') to satisfy T4's requirement for a stated rollback/reversibility mechanism.","cohort":["COH","E1","T4"],"criteria":["T4"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'Mechanism PROVEN (see S0 / eastbound-bald-raptors)' — proven in one spike environment, but no rollback stated for production use.","'fall back to a symlink only if the spike said so' — spike said no symlink, so no fallback is described.","No git-revert or expand-contract step is named."],"finding":"The plan rewrites CLAUDE.md — a file that Claude Code and any agent already configured against this repo reads at launch — removing the bulk of its content and replacing it with a one-line import. No explicit rollback or back-out path is stated if the @AGENTS.md import mechanism does not load correctly in a consumer's environment (e.g., a Claude Code version that interprets @ imports differently).","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f9bb5c28e96f917fb","impact":0.264,"is_primary":null,"location":"De-risking section ('CLAUDE.md = @AGENTS.md + an optional ## Claude Code section'); What section ('reduce CLAUDE.md to a @AGENTS.md import line')","norm_id":"n759f861c343f564f","priority":0.165,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["A Claude Code version shipped after the spike changes @-import semantics; CLAUDE.md now loads nothing useful; all project guidance is silently absent for that agent version.","A consumer using a different Claude Code installation path where @ imports are not supported gets an empty context."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Add a 'Rollback' subsection under De-risking: 'If post-merge verification shows @AGENTS.md fails to load in any supported agent, run `git revert <commit>` on CLAUDE.md to restore full content while the import mechanism is investigated. Verification: after merge, confirm agent context includes AGENTS.md content by checking a known phrase (e.g., \"Serena\") is visible in agent context.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"module","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"low","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"medium","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.75,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Close (transition to `closed`) the spike ticket `eastbound-bald-raptors` so the 'Mechanism PROVEN' assertion is backed by a store-closed ticket, not merely by findings written into an open ticket's description.","cohort":["E4"],"criteria":["E4"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["show_ticket('eastbound-bald-raptors') returns status: 'open', assignee: null","Ticket description says 'This spike is resolved; implementation is a no-op adopt-the-proven-pattern' yet ticket is never transitioned to closed","Plan states definitively: 'DECISION: use the @AGENTS.md import — no symlink fallback needed' based on this spike"],"finding":"The plan asserts 'Mechanism PROVEN (see S0 / eastbound-bald-raptors)' and describes it as 'resolved' in past-tense definitive language, but the ticket `eastbound-bald-raptors` has `status: open` and `assignee: null` in the store. The spike findings are recorded in the ticket description (indicating the spike ran), yet the ticket was never formally closed. The plan treats a not-closed spike as a closed, certified dependency.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f245297882fb6e6ab","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"De-risking results section — 'Mechanism PROVEN (see S0 / eastbound-bald-raptors)'","norm_id":"n5512d426778476f9","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["An executor reading 'Mechanism PROVEN' assumes the spike is fully resolved and the implementation path is locked, but a reviewer checking ticket status would find the spike open and formally uncertified.","If the spike ticket is still open, the dependency the plan describes as settled could be contested or incomplete."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Run `rebar transition eastbound-bald-raptors in_progress closed` (or `open closed`) after confirming the spike's ACs are met — this makes the 'resolved' claim match the store state and satisfies the completion gate that the plan's own rules require.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.5556,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"na","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"yes","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add a step (or AC) to audit existing references to `CLAUDE.md` in READMEs, `CONTRIBUTING.md`, and any onboarding/setup docs, and update them to point to `AGENTS.md`; or note explicitly in the plan that this is deferred with an accepted interim risk.","cohort":["T2","T5e","T7"],"criteria":["T7"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan reduces CLAUDE.md to '≤~30 lines'","No audit or grep step is specified to find files that reference CLAUDE.md as the project's agent-guidance source","The .codex/.agents shims are explicitly deferred: 'the .codex/.agents shims and reference sweep (later story)'","Interim stale window: shims and any cross-referencing docs will point at an empty shell until the later story ships"],"finding":"The plan reduces CLAUDE.md to a thin @AGENTS.md shim but includes no step to audit existing references to CLAUDE.md in other project files (READMEs, CONTRIBUTING.md, onboarding guides, etc.). After the rewrite, those references will point at a nearly empty file, silently misdirecting readers who expect substantive agent guidance there.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f56e6b5bf50ca3c08","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Scope section + AC: 'CLAUDE.md contains exactly one @AGENTS.md import and no duplicated project guidance'","norm_id":"n63b6cbe8ef2ae7d5","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["A contributor reads CONTRIBUTING.md, follows a link to CLAUDE.md for agent guidance, finds only '@AGENTS.md' with no context","An onboarding doc or README that cites CLAUDE.md as 'the agent rules file' becomes silently misleading","The .codex/.agents shims remain stale for an indefinite period between this story and the later sweep story"],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add a Proving step: `rg -l 'CLAUDE\\.md' . --glob '*.md' | xargs grep -l 'CLAUDE\\.md'` and update any references found outside the scope of the .codex/.agents sweep story. If deferral is intentional, add a note in the plan acknowledging the stale-reference window and the later sweep story's responsibility to close it.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.5,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"module","debt_impact":"medium","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"high","prod_impact":"low","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Capture the 'AGENTS.md is canonical; CLAUDE.md is a thin @import shim' architectural decision in a short ADR (e.g., `docs/adr/NNNN-agents-md-canonical.md`) or as a clearly marked design-note section within `AGENTS.md` itself, so the rationale survives beyond the ticket.","cohort":["T2","T5e","T7"],"criteria":["T5e"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'AGENTS.md is read natively by Codex, Cursor, Copilot's coding agent, Zed, Windsurf, Amp, Factory, Jules, Devin, RooCode, and Cline — so a single canonical AGENTS.md covers the ecosystem in one move'","'CLAUDE.md = @AGENTS.md + an optional ## Claude Code section (Anthropic's documented pattern)'","The plan's De-risking section contains the rationale but lives only in the ticket, not in a durable project artifact","No ADR creation is listed in scope or ACs"],"finding":"The plan establishes a novel architectural pattern — AGENTS.md as the single canonical agent-guidance file bridging multiple AI coding ecosystems (Codex, Cursor, Copilot, Zed, Windsurf, Amp, Factory, Jules, Devin, etc.) with CLAUDE.md as a thin import shim — but no ADR or persistent design-doc is planned to capture this decision for future maintainers.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f2198547fb7f7b0e3","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"'Why' section and 'De-risking results' section","norm_id":"nd68bb404dec0b94a","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["A future maintainer sees CLAUDE.md is nearly empty and wonders if it was accidentally truncated","A new contributor doesn't understand why AGENTS.md is the canonical file instead of CLAUDE.md and re-expands CLAUDE.md","The 'Why' rationale is lost if the ticket/plan is archived or not easily searchable"],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add a `## Design note` or `## Why this file` block at the top of AGENTS.md (3–5 lines) explaining the canonical-file pattern and listing the ecosystems it covers, so the rationale is co-located with the artifact. Alternatively, create a minimal ADR in `docs/adr/`.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.2857,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"na","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Enumerate and update (or explicitly defer with rationale) all files outside the repo root that link to or describe CLAUDE.md sections being removed — at minimum: README.md#ticket-template anchor, docs/api-stability.md MCP tool-set reference, docs/architecture.md, docs/workflow-engine.md, CONTRIBUTING.md, rebar.toml comment.","cohort":["G1G2"],"criteria":["G1G2"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["README.md:354 — hardcoded anchor link `[CLAUDE.md](CLAUDE.md#ticket-template-the-gates-enforce)` to a section that will be removed from CLAUDE.md","docs/api-stability.md:25 — 'the documented tool set in [CLAUDE.md](../CLAUDE.md)' — after rewrite, the MCP tool set lives in docs/mcp-reference.md, making this description stale","docs/architecture.md:233 — 'the agent-facing tool set and workflow are in `CLAUDE.md`'","CONTRIBUTING.md:570 — 'Track your work in rebar (see [`CLAUDE.md`](CLAUDE.md) and [`docs/`](docs/))'","rebar.toml:3 — comment 'See docs/llm-framework.md and CLAUDE.md for the close gate + LLM module'","docs/workflow-engine.md:29 — '(see the project guide / `CLAUDE.md`)'","docs/jira-sync-setup.md:484 — references CLAUDE.md","docs/exit-codes.md:43 — references CLAUDE.md"],"finding":"Several callers outside the repo root reference `CLAUDE.md` by section anchor or by description in ways that break semantically when CLAUDE.md is gutted to a thin `@AGENTS.md` import — none are enumerated as consumers requiring update.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f7725e8fc56091149","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Scope section ('In: new AGENTS.md, rewritten CLAUDE.md'); also the original and revised Acceptance Criteria","norm_id":"ndb054acd058c7a5c","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":["README.md's anchor `CLAUDE.md#ticket-template-the-gates-enforce` becomes a dead anchor once CLAUDE.md contains only an import line and an optional Claude Code section.","docs/api-stability.md continues to describe the MCP tool set as living in CLAUDE.md even though it will have been moved to docs/mcp-reference.md, creating a misleading stability contract reference for external consumers."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.5,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"ye